      "text": "Using sensors (to detect water level, pH and temperature), microprocessors (mostly the open-source Arduino microcontroller), relay cards, clouds and social media networks, Maundu has programmed his gardens to tweet when there’s a problem (e.g. not enough water) or when there’s news (e.g. an over-abundance of food to share) - [http://faircompanies.com/videos/internet-of-food-arduino-based-urban-aquaponics-in-oakland/ faircompanies.com]"
